The paper discusses the evaluation of personalization for information retrieval, which is a core topic in information retrieval (cs.IR). The paper also emphasizes the importance of considering the search session as a whole and the variety of activities that people engage in during an information search session, which are key issues in human-computer interaction (cs.HC). The paper also mentions the need for data concerning searcher and system behavior, which is relevant to natural language processing (cs.CL), cybernetics (cs.CY), and cryptography and security (cs.CR) as well.
